div.p:
               LONDON;
Printed by Matthew Simmons in Alderſgate-ſtreete.
1645.

Brethren, we ſay, that Omni & nulli credere, utrum
que nefas, for to beleeve all the falſe miracles of Papiſts; as of the coming of ſoules out of Purgatory, which is but the deluſion of the Devill, were evill;
and for me not to beleeve this of the Thorne, were alſo naught. Becauſe for theſe Reaſons, I am bound to beleeve it.
